		<h3>Bolivia, a wonderful country... a country with needs</h3><br>
		<p>
			Bolivia has a population of 10,059,856 (2012 census), about 4 million people are under the age of 18. Nearly 2.9 million living children and adolescents are affected by: injustice, exclusion, social inequality, exploitation, discrimination and poverty.
		</p><br>
		<p>
			While primary school enrollment rates remain above 90%, the completion rate for primary school is 56%. UDAPE 2013.
		</p><br>
		<p>
			There are an estimated 210,000 orphans and 366,000 abandoned. 850,000 children and adolescents work at least one hour a day and more than 1,000 are living in prison with their parents.  2,200 are living on the street, 1.2 million have been physically punished and 1.1 million have been subjected to psychological violence.
		</p><br>
		<p>
			Infant mortality was 50 per one thousand live births in 2008. 87% of the population has access to an improved water source. 63% of the population has access to an improved sanitation system (UDAPE 2013). Finally, between 2008 and 2010 social spending for children was increased from 7.8% to 8% of GDP (UDAPE 2012).
		</p><br><br>
